there are 171,476 words in english, yet i can't seem to find the right word to describe what i feel when you look at me. i can't seem to find the right word to describe the way i smile when you kiss me. it feels like the perfect metaphor for the poem which i have been trying to write for a long time, and every word you speak is bleeding poetry that i want to save for rainy days. 
love, let me drown, let me form galaxies on your skin. allow me to learn the way your eyes shift when they talk about the things you like. allow me to learn about your favourite things, and things that you hate. 
i will love you tenderly, on skins and words on collarbones. hearts in cupped hands and poems in our pockets. i will love you faithfully, fighting the hurricanes on cold night, standing by your side during storms.  i will love you endlessly, kiss your every scar and embrace your flaws. 
i picture us growing old, you're the one that will be by my side when i am old and wrinkly, and i'll be the one you'll see when you pull that veil over your head. i picture the scattered laughter on pavement, stripped sanity, silly inside jokes and sneaky kisses. i picture whispered thoughts during late night and our love through the dotted silence when no words are needed. 
i love you. and i can't think of anything else that matters anymore. because it's just you in the end, let me be your forever (via @110years on ig)

@SoulBraille • "That kind of love that’s “I was scared until I found you.” that kind of love that’s worth it to try romance again. The “fuck i’ll try cheesy if it just makes you smile” love, the roses and love notes and wine bottles. the twinkle light love, the “let’s go on this romantic date only to spend the whole thing being silly” love, the dancing badly to slow songs love, the “I don’t know how you make me laugh so much but seriously stop it, i’m trying to drive” love. the “I trust you love,” calling late at night because a secret just welled up in my throat love, the first person I talk to so I can figure out this decision is you kind of love. The “I was hurt before and had given up but then I found you” love, the incredulous in-awe love, the wonder love, the are you actually real or am I dreaming you love. the “I didn’t believe in soulmates before you” love. That kinda love." Unknown (via @soulbraille #soulbraille) 🖤
